BSWMG In The News

2016 Five Star Wealth Manager Award
      Diana Joseph/BSWMG honored as a five year winner (2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, and 2016) of Five Star Wealth Manager in the November issue of Chicago Magazine
Press Release � November 17, 2016

 11/9/16 WBBM Newsradio 780’s Kris Kridel interviews Diana Joseph for “Personal Finance Wednesday: Navigating Your Investments in a Time of Political Change”
      During the interview, Diana emphasized the prematurity of making big changes in client portfolios as a result of the Trump presidential win. “Now is the time to sit back and let the dust settle,” while creating an outline of possible moves with information that is known. Diana drew attention to interest rates and the impact of a rise in rates on savings, bonds, and mortgages. Diana also mentioned healthcare and biotech, energy, and defense as favored sectors under the coming administration.  In summary, Diana reiterated the importance of client asset allocations which were created with individual goals in mind, so portfolio changes would be made slowly and incrementally. The “Navigating Your Investments” section begins at the 20 minute mark.
Click here to listen.

8/17/2016 Diana Joseph spoke during the Private Wealth Midwest Forum in Chicago, IL.
        Diana participated in a roundtable discussion on the topic of “Advanced Asset Allocation.”  Conference organizer Markets Group brought together regional thought leaders in the high-net-worth community to exchange their insights and experiences.

3/10/2016 Diana Joseph presented to the Lake Forest Estate Planning Council, Lake Forest, IL.
        “Economic/Investment Outlook”

