 2014 Five Star Wealth Manager Award
      Diana Joseph/BSWMG honored as a three year winner (2012, 2013 and 2014) of Five Star Wealth Manager in the November issue of Chicago Magazine
Press Release � November 17, 2014

Diana Joseph quoted in Barron’s
      Dow Slides 2.75%, Into the Red for the Year
      By JACQUELINE DOHERTY
      “This is the beginning of a little taper tantrum,” says Diana in the article. As the Fed’s quantitative easing program slows, investors are noticing the value of holdings in their portfolios more. Small caps, as measured by the Russell 2000 Growth Index, are down year-to-date compared to large caps, which are up.  The Russell 1000 Growth Index’s earnings multiple of 18 is significantly lower than that of the Russell 2000’s Growth Index at 30.  Large Caps are better priced for the moment; “valuation disparities are great.” With the Fed’s fund flows ebbing, the “anything goes” equity strategy has dried up. Hard commodities, large-cap stocks with growing dividends, and some munis have more attractive risk/reward profiles.
Barron’s – August 2, 2014

